  "notes": "Curitibano / Paranaense (Curitiba, Paran√°). Transitional SulistaвАУPaulistano. Encoded conservative default: non-palatalising /t,d/ and final /e/ often retained as [e] (the well-documented Curitiba 'e/o fechados'), with palatalisation present in younger and Paulista-influenced speech (noted). Coda /S/ alveolar; coda /R/ tap. Heterogeneous: Curitiba diverges from the more caipira-like Paran√° interior. Slavic/Italian settler substrata. This spec models the Curitiba/Sulista-type coda /r/ as an alveolar tap […Њ]; the retroflex 'r caipira' (Amaral 1920 ¬І6b) is instead characteristic of the northern/interior Paran√° hinterland, which patterns with pt-BR-x-caipira.",
